<div class="met-hero">
    <span class="met-pill">Compliance & Architecture</span>
    <h2>No EMR replacement. HIPAA-eligible from day one. Pilot in weeks, not quarters.</h2>
    <p>Avail keeps the EMR they already use. We add a thin layer on top that turns consult recordings, lab data, and prior notes into <strong>draft protocols</strong> and <strong>cohort intelligence</strong>. Nothing is auto-sent. The provider always reviews and signs off.</p>
</div>

<!-- Architecture diagram -->
<div class="met-section">
    <h3>The flow</h3>
    <div class="met-flow">
        <div class="met-step">
            <div class="met-step-num">1</div>
            <div class="met-step-icon">{% icon "mic", "met-step-svg", 24 %}</div>
            <h4>Capture consult</h4>
            <p>Patient signs a one-page consent. Brooke records on her phone or laptop. Auto-uploads to a HIPAA-compliant intake.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="met-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="met-step">
            <div class="met-step-num">2</div>
            <div class="met-step-icon">{% icon "lock", "met-step-svg", 24 %}</div>
            <h4>Secure transcribe</h4>
            <p>Audio → text via a HIPAA-eligible transcription service (AWS Transcribe Medical, Azure Speech, or Whisper on a HIPAA-eligible host). PHI stays inside the BAA boundary.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="met-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="met-step">
            <div class="met-step-num">3</div>
            <div class="met-step-icon">{% icon "brain", "met-step-svg", 24 %}</div>
            <h4>Cohort match + draft</h4>
            <p>De-identified vector search across past patients. Claude (via AWS Bedrock w/ BAA) drafts the protocol with rationale and source citations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="met-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="met-step">
            <div class="met-step-num">4</div>
            <div class="met-step-icon">{% icon "check-circle", "met-step-svg", 24 %}</div>
            <h4>Provider review</h4>
            <p>Brooke or Nicki reviews the draft, edits, approves. Only then does anything reach the patient. Sign-off is logged.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Compliance grid -->
<div class="met-section">
    <h3>Compliance posture</h3>
    <div class="met-comp-grid">
        <div class="met-comp">
            <div class="met-comp-head">{% icon "lock", "met-head-svg", 18 %} HIPAA</div>
            <ul>
                <li>BAAs signed with every vendor that touches PHI (AWS, Anthropic, transcription provider).</li>
                <li>PHI stored only in HIPAA-eligible services (AWS HealthLake / S3 with encryption + audit).</li>
                <li>De-identification before any cohort/analytics use (Safe Harbor method, 18 identifiers stripped).</li>
                <li>Role-based access · audit logs on every read · session timeouts · MFA required.</li>
                <li>Minimum-necessary principle: AI gets only the data it needs for the specific draft.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="met-comp">
            <div class="met-comp-head">{% icon "credit-card", "met-head-svg", 18 %} PCI</div>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>We don't touch payments.</strong> Avail keeps using their existing billing system.</li>
                <li>PCI scope for this product = zero. If billing ever connects, it's via a tokenized handoff to a Level-1 PCI provider (Stripe, Square).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="met-comp">
            <div class="met-comp-head">{% icon "scroll", "met-head-svg", 18 %} Consent</div>
            <ul>
                <li>One-page recording consent added to existing intake. Patient can opt out anytime.</li>
                <li>De-identified cohort data only — patients are never identifiable in trend views.</li>
                <li>Pilot starts with 5–10 patients who explicitly opt in. Easy to expand once Brooke is comfortable.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="met-comp">
            <div class="met-comp-head">{% icon "life-buoy", "met-head-svg", 18 %} Liability</div>
            <ul>
                <li>The system <strong>drafts</strong> — it does not prescribe. Provider sign-off is mandatory and logged.</li>
                <li>All sources cited — Brooke can see exactly which past patient or note influenced the draft.</li>
                <li>Watch-fors flagged automatically (drug interactions, abnormal labs, contraindications).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Phased rollout -->
<div class="met-section">
    <h3>Pilot path · low risk, fast to value</h3>
    <div class="met-phases">
        <div class="met-phase">
            <div class="met-phase-tag" style="background: #dcfce7; color: #166534;">Phase 1 · Weeks 1–4</div>
            <h4>Manual workflow pilot</h4>
            <p>5 opted-in patients. Brooke records consult, uploads to intake form. Within 24 hours, AI returns draft protocol via secure email. <strong>No EMR integration. No live system. Just proof of value.</strong></p>
            <div class="met-phase-cost">Investment: ~40 build hrs · ~$200/mo infra</div>
        </div>
        <div class="met-phase">
            <div class="met-phase-tag" style="background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af;">Phase 2 · Weeks 5–12</div>
            <h4>Automated pipeline + cohort dashboard</h4>
            <p>Direct upload from phone. Real-time draft (under 60 sec). Patient persona dashboard live. Brooke can pull protocols by cohort.</p>
            <div class="met-phase-cost">Investment: ~120 build hrs · ~$400/mo infra (scales with usage)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="met-phase">
            <div class="met-phase-tag" style="background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e;">Phase 3 · Optional</div>
            <h4>EMR read-only integration</h4>
            <p>If/when valuable: pull patient context from existing EMR via API (read-only, scoped). Still no EMR replacement. Brooke retains the system she already trusts.</p>
            <div class="met-phase-cost">Investment: scoped after phase 2 results</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Tools used -->
<div class="met-section">
    <h3>Tools we'd use (HIPAA-eligible)</h3>
    <div class="met-tools">
        <div class="met-tool">
            <strong>Anthropic Claude via AWS Bedrock</strong>
            <span>LLM with BAA · the engine that drafts protocols</span>
        </div>
        <div class="met-tool">
            <strong>AWS Transcribe Medical</strong>
            <span>Medical-vocabulary speech-to-text · HIPAA-eligible</span>
        </div>
        <div class="met-tool">
            <strong>AWS S3 + KMS</strong>
            <span>Encrypted storage · audit-logged · BAA</span>
        </div>
        <div class="met-tool">
            <strong>Pinecone (HIPAA-eligible tier) or pgvector</strong>
            <span>De-identified embeddings for cohort matching</span>
        </div>
        <div class="met-tool">
            <strong>Existing EMR</strong>
            <span>Stays put · no replacement · optional read-only API later</span>
        </div>
        <div class="met-tool">
            <strong>Existing billing</strong>
            <span>Untouched · zero PCI scope</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

